value.value: Melanophilin (600 aa, ~66 kDa) is encoded by the human MLPH gene. This protein is involved in melanin transport.
This gene plays a role in kinetochore assembly and microtubule organization.

Human NDC80 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 18p11.32 and is approximately 45 kb in length. This allele, which encodes kinetochore protein NDC80 homolog protein, is involved in chromosome segregation and mitotic spindle checkpoint activity.
Kinetochore protein NDC80 homolog (642 aa, ~74 kDa) is encoded by the human NDC80 gene. This protein plays a role in the attachment of mitotic spindle microtubules to the kinetochore.
This gene may be involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

Human GPR160 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3q26.2 and is approximately 48 kb in length. This allele, which encodes probable G-protein coupled receptor 160 protein, may play a role in G protein-coupled receptor signaling.
Probable G-protein coupled receptor 160 (338 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human GPR160 gene. This protein may be involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling.
An algorithm designed to categorize  analgesic medication use, and capture changes in the dosing, frequency, and/or type of analgesic medications administered.
A response that indicates the patient did not use any analgesic.
A response that indicates the patient used a non-opioid analgesic.
A response that indicates the patient used weak opioids.

label.value: Strong Opioids Less than or Equal to 75 mg Oral Morphine Equivalent per Day

value.value: A response that indicates the patient used strong opioids at less than or equal to 75 mg oral morphine equivalents (OME) per day.

label.value: Strong Opioids Greater than 75-150 mg Oral Morphine Equivalent per Day

value.value: A response that indicates the patient used strong opioids at greater than 75 mg to a maximum of 150 mg oral morphine equivalents (OME) per day.

label.value: Strong Opioids Greater than 150-300 mg Oral Morphine Equivalent per Day

value.value: A response that indicates the patient used strong opioids at greater than 150 mg to a maximum of 300 mg oral morphine equivalents (OME) per day.

label.value: Strong Opioids Greater than 300-600 mg Oral Morphine Equivalent per Day

value.value: A response that indicates the patient used strong opioids at greater than 300 mg to a maximum of 600 mg oral morphine equivalents (OME) per day.

label.value: Strong Opioids Greater than 600 mg Oral Morphine Equivalent per Day

value.value: A response that indicates the patient used strong opioids at greater than 600 mg oral morphine equivalents (OME) per day.
This gene plays a role in the regulation of apoptosis, signaling pathways and gene expression.

Human CXXC5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 5q31.2 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes CXXC-type zinc finger protein 5, is involved in the modulation of signaling, the regulation of apoptosis and transcriptional regulation.
CXXC-type zinc finger protein 5 (322 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human CXXC5 gene. This protein plays a role in transcriptional regulation.
A procedure that utilizes a computerized algorithm to directly determine aperture intensities for optimal radiation dose distributions associated with intensity-modulated radiotherapy (IMRT).
A procedure that utilizes manual determinations of beam angles and aperture exposure time to optimize radiation dose distributions associated with intensity-modulated radiotherapy (IMRT).
A two-dimensional (2D) array of opposing, oblique beams of external radiation. This approach is most often used in the adjuvant radiotherapy of breast malignancies.
An adenocarcinoma arising from the lower third of the esophagus. The vast majority of esophageal adenocarcinomas involve the lower third of the esophagus.
This gene is involved in the conversion of biliverdin to bilirubin.

Human BLVRA wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7p13 and is approximately 49 kb in length. This allele, which encodes biliverdin reductase A protein, plays a role in protoheme degradation. Truncation mutations in the gene are associated with hyperbiliverdinemia.
Biliverdin reductase A (296 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human BLVRA gene. This protein is involved in the reduction of biliverdin IX alpha.

An alternative medical system that focuses on the relationship between bodily structure (primarily that of the spine) and function, and how that relationship affects the preservation and restoration of health. Chiropractors use manipulative therapy as an integral treatment tool.
This gene may play a role in actin binding and organization of the cytoskeleton.
Human ACTR3B wild-type allele is located within 7q36.1-q36.2 and is approximately 128 kb in length. This allele, which encodes actin-related protein 3B, is involved in cytoskeletal organization.
Actin-related protein 3B (418 aa, ~48 kDa) is encoded by the human ACTR3B gene. This protein plays a role in actin binding and organization of the cytoskeleton.
This gene is involved in the conversion of proline and ornithine to glutamate.

Human ALDH4A1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p36.13 and is approximately 31 kb in length. This allele, which encodes delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase protein, mitochondrial, plays a role in glutamate synthesis. Mutation of the gene is associated with type II hyperprolinemia.

Delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase, mitochondrial (563 aa, ~62 kDa) is encoded by the human ALDH4A1 gene. This protein is involved in the conversion of proline pyrroline-5-carboxylate to glutamate.
Primary peritoneal carcinoma that is resistant to treatment.
Fallopian tube carcinoma that is resistant to treatment.
Female reproductive system carcinoma that is resistant to treatment.
This gene plays a role in protein transport via clathrin-coated vesicles.
Role of cholesterol in cancer causation or prevention and in general health.

Human AP2B1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q12 and is approximately 148 kb in length. This allele, which encodes AP-2 complex subunit beta protein, is involved in endocytosis mediated by clathrin-coated vesicles.
AP-2 complex subunit beta (937 aa, ~105 kDa) is encoded by the human AP2B1 gene. This protein plays a role in formation of and cargo selection for clathrin-coated vesicles.
A radiation therapy technique where treatment is emitted along the central axis of an external radiation beam.

A radiation therapy technique used to treat breast malignancies where the treatment fields are wide superiorly to include the internal mammary nodes, but narrow inferiorly to reduce radiation exposure to the heart and lung.
A radiation therapy technique where external electron beams are used to deliver treatment to superficial malignancies while sparing underlying organs at risk.

label.value: Direct Mixed Photon and Electron Field

value.value: A radiation therapy technique where external photon and electron beams are used to deliver treatment of superficial and deep-seated malignancies, respectively, while sparing underlying organs at risk.
A SI derived unit of electric potential and electromotive force that is equal to one million volts.
A unit of energy that is equal to one million electron volts.
This gene is involved in the conversion of lysophosphatidylcholine to phosphatidylcholine.

Human LPCAT1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 5p15.33 and is approximately 69 kb in length. This allele, which encodes lysophosphatidylcholine acyltransferase 1 protein, plays a role in phosphatidylcholine biosynthesis.
